Plug-in name: Mthread
Plug-in shortname: mt
Description: Experimental tools for multi-threaded programs

Most options of the form '-mt-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-mt-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-mt-share <dir>     set the plug-in share directory to <dir> (may be used if
                    the plug-in is not installed at the same place as
                    Frama-C)
-mthread            enable analysis of multi-threaded programs through the
                    Mthread plugin (opposite option is -no-mthread)

*** ANALYSIS

-mt-interrupt-handlers <functions>  Specify functions that will be treated as
                    handlers for interrupts. (preferably use
                    -mt-interrupt-handlers="functions")
-mt-shared-accesses-synchronization  more precise inference of which mutexes
                    protect shared memory (opposite option is
                    -mt-no-shared-accesses-synchronization)
-mt-shared-values <level>  Show what threads read and write in shared memory
                    at the end of each iteration
                    0: values not shown
                    1: values shown
                    2: values shown with the stack at which the operation
                    occurs
-mt-threads-lib <builtins-only|pthreads>  Select which threading library is
                    stubbed by MThread. Defaults to "builtins-only".
-mt-write-races     Display memory on which there is a write-only race
                    condition (opposite option is -mt-no-write-races)

*** DEBUG

-mt-concat-dot-files-to <filename>  Concatenate dot files generated by the
                    html output into a single file.
-mt-consider-null   (set by default) opposite of option -mt-ignore-null,
                    whose help message is:
                    Ignore shared accesses to numeric memory (NULL base)
-mt-debug <n>       level of debug for plug-in Mthread (default to 0)
-mt-ignore-null     Ignore shared accesses to numeric memory (NULL base)
                    (opposite option is -mt-consider-null)
-mt-keep-dot-files  Keep dot files used to generate SVG for the html output
                    (opposite option is -mt-no-keep-dot-files)
-mt-only-threads <th1,...,thn>  only execute the specified threads
                    (preferably use -mt-only-threads="th1,...,thn")
-mt-projects-on-disk  After each thread analysis, save the current analysis
                    state in a separate file (opposite option is
                    -mt-no-projects-on-disk)
-mt-projects-on-disk-prefix <prefix>  Prepend <prefix> to the project's
                    filename saved by -mt-projects-on-disk (defaults to
                    mthread_) (preferably use
                    -mt-projects-on-disk-prefix="prefix")
-mt-skip-threads <th1,...,thn>  do not execute the specified threads
                    (preferably use -mt-skip-threads="th1,...,thn")
-mt-stop-after <i>  Only perform at most i iterations

*** EXTRACTION OF MODELS

-mt-extract <[html]>  extraction of models (preferably use
                    -mt-extract="[html]")

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-mt-help            help of plug-in Mthread
-mt-h               alias for option -mt-help

*** MULTITHREADED CONTROL-FLOW-GRAPH

-mt-full-cfg        Do not simplify cfg and show all statements (can be
                    costly) (opposite option is -mt-no-full-cfg)
-mt-non-concurrent-accesses  Keep non-concurrent accesses to shared variables
                    in the cfg (set by default, opposite option is
                    -mt-no-non-concurrent-accesses)
-mt-non-shared-accesses  Keep accesses to false shared variables in the cfg
                    (opposite option is -mt-no-non-shared-accesses)
-mt-return-edges    Show link between a call an a return instruction as a
                    dotted line (set by default, opposite option is
                    -mt-no-return-edges)

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-mt-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Mthread to a file. <K> is a
                    combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -mt-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-mt-moderate-warnings  Show semi-important warnings during analysis. (set by
                    default, opposite option is -mt-no-moderate-warnings)
-mt-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -mt-msg-key help to get a list of
                    available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -mt-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-mt-print-callstacks  Print the callstacks at which concurrent events occur
                    (opposite option is -mt-no-print-callstacks)
-mt-verbose <n>     level of verbosity for plug-in Mthread (default to 1)
-mt-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category <k1> to
                    <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -mt-warn-key help to get a
                    list of available categories, and * to enable all
                    categories. Possible statuses are inactive, feedback,
                    warning, error, abort, feedback-once, warning-once,
                    error-once. Defaults to warning. (preferably use
                    -mt-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
